                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title2" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"ID-2242-000001bc">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title2">A=
bout <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</spa=
n></span> High Availability
                     </h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                        <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2242-000001bc__ID-2242-0000=
01d7">To ensure the continuity of operations, the high availability
                           		feature allows you to designate redundant=20
                           		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepowe=
r Management Center</span></span>s
                           		to manage devices.=20
                           		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepowe=
r Management Center</span></span>s
                           		support Active/Standby high availability where=
 one appliance is the active unit
                           		and manages devices. The standby unit does not=
 actively manage devices. The
                           		active unit writes configuration data into a d=
ata store and replicates data for
                           		both units, using synchronization where necess=
ary to share some information
                           		with the standby unit.=20
                           	=20
                        </p>
                        <p class=3D"p">Active/Standby high availability let=
s you configure a secondary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower=
 Management Center</span></span> to take over the functionality of a primar=
y <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span><=
/span> if the primary fails. When the primary <span class=3D"ph"><span clas=
s=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> fails, you must promote =
the secondary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Ce=
nter</span></span> to become the active unit.=20
                        </p>
                        <p class=3D"p">Event data streams from managed devi=
ces to both <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Cent=
er</span></span>s in the high availability pair. If one <span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> fails, you can=
 monitor your network without interruption using the other <span class=3D"p=
h"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>.=20
                        </p>
                        <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2242-000001bc__ID-2242-0000=
022b">Note that=20
                           		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepowe=
r Management Center</span></span>s
                           		configured as a high availability pair do not =
need to be on the same trusted
                           		management network, nor do they have to be in =
the same geographic location.=20
                           	=20
                        </p>
                        <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"olh_n=
ote" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                           <tbody><tr>
                              <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=3D"h=
eading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/us/td=
/i/templates/caut.gif"><br><p><b>Caution</b></p>
                              </td>
                              <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                 <section class=3D"note__content">
                                    <hr>=20
                                    	=09
                                    <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2242-000001bc__=
ID-2242-000001dd">Because the system restricts some functionality to the ac=
tive=20
                                       		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>,
                                       		  if that appliance fails, you mus=
t promote the standby=20
                                       		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>
                                       		  to active.=20
                                       	=09
                                    </p>=20
                                    	=20
                                    <hr>
                                 </section>
                              </td>
                           </tr>
                        </tbody></table></div>
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"ID-2242-000001bc__=
section_t5s_hz5_jz">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">About Remote Ac=
cess VPN High Availability</h3>
                           		=09
                           		=09
                           <p class=3D"p">If the primary device has Remote =
Access VPN configuration with an identity certificate enrolled using a Cert=
Enrollment object,
                              the secondary device must have an identity ce=
rtificate enrolled using the same CertEnrollment object. The CertEnrollment=
 object
                              can have different values for the primary and=
 secondary devices due to device-specific overriddes. The limitation is onl=
y
                              to have the same CertEnrollment object enroll=
ed on the two devices before the high availability formation.
                           </p>
                           	=09
                        </section>
                        	=09
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"ID-2242-000001bc__=
section_t5s_hz5_jz_d805e90a1310">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">SNMP Behavior i=
n <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span><=
/span> High Availability=20
                           </h3>
                           		=09
                           		=09
                           <p class=3D"p">In an SNMP-configured HA pair, wh=
en you deploy an alert policy, the primary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> sends the SNMP traps. Whe=
n the primary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Ce=
nter</span></span> fails, the secondary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">Firepower Management Center</span></span>, which becomes the active unit=
, sends the SNMP traps without the need for any additional configuration.
                           </p>
                           	=09
                        </section>
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->

                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title3" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_21173">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title3=
">Roles v. Status in Firepower Management Center High Availability</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_21173__secti=
on_nh1_xny_yy">
                              <h4 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Primary/Seco=
ndary Roles </h4>
                              		=09
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p">When setting up <span class=3D=
"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s in a hig=
h availability pair, you configure one <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
">Firepower Management Center</span></span> to be primary and the other as =
secondary. During configuration, the primary unit's policies are synchroniz=
ed to the secondary
                                 unit. After this synchronization, the prim=
ary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span=
></span> becomes the active peer, while the secondary <span class=3D"ph"><s=
pan class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> becomes the stan=
dby peer, and the two units act as a single appliance for managed device an=
d policy configuration.
                              </p>
                              	=09
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_21173__secti=
on_rv2_f4y_yy">
                              <h4 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Active/Stand=
by Status</h4>
                              		=09
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p">The main differences between t=
he two <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</s=
pan></span>s in a high availability pair are related to which peer is activ=
e and which peer is standby. The active <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"p=
h">Firepower Management Center</span></span> remains fully functional, wher=
e you can manage devices and policies. On the standby <span class=3D"ph"><s=
pan class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>, functionality i=
s hidden; you cannot make any configuration changes.
                              </p>
                              	=09
                           </section>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title4" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_21208">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title4=
">Event Processing on
                           	 Firepower Management Center High Availability =
Pairs
                        </h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p"> Since both <span class=3D"ph"><s=
pan class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s in a high avail=
ability pair receive events from managed devices, the management IP address=
es for the appliances are not
                              shared. This means that you do not need to in=
tervene to ensure continuous processing of events if a <span class=3D"ph"><=
span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> fails.=20
                           </p>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links">
                           <ul class=3D"ullinks">
                              <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guid=
e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower_management_center_high_availability.html#=
id_21199">AMP Cloud Connections and Malware Information</a></li>
                              <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guid=
e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower_management_center_high_availability.html#=
id_21206">URL Filtering and Security Intelligence</a></li>
                           </ul>
                        </nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                        <article class=3D"topic concept nested3" aria-label=
ledby=3D"ariaid-title5" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_21199">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le5">AMP Cloud
                              	 Connections and Malware Information
                           </h4>
                           <section class=3D"body conbody">
                              <p class=3D"p">Although they share
                                 		file policies and related configurations=
,=20
                                 		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fi=
repower Management Center</span></span>s
                                 		in a high availability pair share neithe=
r Cisco AMP cloud connections nor
                                 		malware dispositions. To ensure continui=
ty of operations, and to ensure that
                                 		detected files=E2=80=99 malware disposit=
ions are the same on both=20
                                 		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fi=
repower Management Center</span></span>s,
                                 		both primary and secondary=20
                                 		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fi=
repower Management Center</span></span>s
                                 		must have access to the AMP cloud.=20
                                 	=20
                              </p>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic concept nested3" aria-label=
ledby=3D"ariaid-title6" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_21206">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le6">URL Filtering and
                              	 Security Intelligence
                           </h4>
                           <section class=3D"body conbody">
                              <p class=3D"p">URL filtering and
                                 		Security Intelligence configurations and=
 information are synchronized between=20
                                 		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fi=
repower Management Center</span></span>s
                                 		in a high availability deployment. Howev=
er, only the primary=20
                                 		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fi=
repower Management Center</span></span>
                                 		downloads URL category and reputation da=
ta for updates to Security Intelligence
                                 		feeds.=20
                                 	=20
                              </p>
                              <p class=3D"p">If the primary=20
                                 		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fi=
repower Management Center</span></span>
                                 		fails, not only must you make sure that =
the secondary=20
                                 		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fi=
repower Management Center</span></span>
                                 		can access the internet to update threat=
 intelligence data, but you must also
                                 		use the web interface on the secondary=
=20
                                 		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fi=
repower Management Center</span></span>
                                 		to promote it to active.=20
                                 	=20
                              </p>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title7" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_21208">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title7=
">User Data Processing
                           During Firepower Management Center Failover
                        </h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p">If the primary <span class=3D"ph"=
><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> fails, the Se=
condary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</=
span></span> propagates to managed devices user-to-IP mappings from the <sp=
an class=3D"ph">TS Agent </span> identity source<span class=3D"ph">; and pr=
opagates SGT mappings from the ISE<span class=3D"ph">/ISE-PIC</span> identi=
ty source</span>. Users not yet seen by identity sources are identified as =
Unknown.
                           </p>
                           <p class=3D"p">After the downtime, the Unknown u=
sers are re identified and processed according to the rules in
                              your identity policy.=20
                           </p>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title8" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_21209">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title8=
">Configuration
                           	 Management on Firepower Management Center High=
 Availability Pairs
                        </h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p"> In a high
                              		availability deployment, only the active=20
                              		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firep=
ower Management Center</span></span>
                              		can manage devices and apply policies. Both=
=20
                              		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firep=
ower Management Center</span></span>s
                              		remain in a state of continuous synchroniza=
tion.=20
                              	=20
                           </p>
                           <p class=3D"p">If the active=20
                              		<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firep=
ower Management Center</span></span>
                              		fails, the high availability pair enters a =
degraded state until you manually
                              		promote the standby appliance to the active=
 state. Once the promotion is
                              		complete, the appliances leave maintenance =
mode.
                              	=20
                           </p>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links">
                           <ul class=3D"ullinks">
                              <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guid=
e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower_management_center_high_availability.html#=
id_62882">Threat Intelligence Director and High Availability Configurations=
</a></li>
                              <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guid=
e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower_management_center_high_availability.html#=
Cisco_Concept.dita_f5f8ace6-40da-414d-aa2c-e97c68cc94d9">Single Sign-On and=
 High Availability Pairs</a></li>
                           </ul>
                        </nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                        <article class=3D"topic concept nested3" aria-label=
ledby=3D"ariaid-title9" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_62882">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le9"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Threat Intelligence Director</sp=
an></span> and High Availability Configurations
                           </h4>
                           <section class=3D"body conbody">
                              <p class=3D"p">If you host <span class=3D"ph"=
><span class=3D"ph">TID</span></span> on the active <span class=3D"ph"><spa=
n class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> in a high availabi=
lity configuration, the system does not synchronize <span class=3D"ph"><spa=
n class=3D"ph">TID</span></span> configurations and <span class=3D"ph"><spa=
n class=3D"ph">TID</span></span> data to the standby <span class=3D"ph"><sp=
an class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>. We recommend per=
forming regular backups of <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">TID</span>=
</span> data on your active <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower=
 Management Center</span></span> so that you can restore the data after fai=
lover.
                              </p>
                              <p class=3D"p">For details, see <a class=3D"x=
ref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/co=
nfiguration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/cisco_threat_intelligence_director.=
html#concept_ysb_t25_5y">About Backing Up and Restoring TID Data</a>.
                              </p>
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
></nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                        <article class=3D"topic concept nested3" aria-label=
ledby=3D"ariaid-title10" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"Cisco_Concept.dita_f5f8ace6-4=
0da-414d-aa2c-e97c68cc94d9">
                           <h4 class=3D"title topictitle4" id=3D"ariaid-tit=
le10">Single Sign-On and High Availability Pairs</h4>
                           <section class=3D"body conbody">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>s in a high availability configuration can support=
 Single Sign-On, but you must keep
                                 the following considerations in mind:
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <ul class=3D"ul">
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">SSO configuration is not=
 synchronized between the members of the high
                                       availability pair; you must configur=
e SSO separately on each member of the
                                       pair.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Both <span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>s in a high availability pari must use =
the same identity provider (IdP) for
                                       SSO. You must configure a service pr=
ovider application at the IdP for each <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
">FMC</span></span> configured for SSO.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">In a high availabilty pa=
ir of <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>s where both a=
re configured to support SSO, before a user can use SSO to
                                       access the secondary <span class=3D"=
ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> for the first time, that user must=
 first use SSO to log into the primary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
">FMC</span></span> at least once.=20
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">When configuring SSO for=
 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>s in a high availab=
ility pair:
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                    <ul class=3D"ul">
                                      =20
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">If you configure S=
SO on the primary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>, =
you are not required to configure SSO on the secondary <span class=3D"ph"><=
span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>.
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </li>
                                      =20
                                       <li class=3D"li">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p">If you configure S=
SO on the secondary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>=
, you are required to configure SSO on the primary <span class=3D"ph"><span=
 class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> as well. (This is because SSO users must lo=
g in to the primary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>=
 at least once before logging into the secondary <span class=3D"ph"><span c=
lass=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>.)
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </li>
                                      =20
                                    </ul>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                              </ul>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <!-- minitoc start -->
                           <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"=
>
                              <section class=3D"linklist relinfo relconcept=
s"><strong>Related Concepts</strong><br><section><a class=3D"link" href=3D"=
https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/g=
uide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/user_accounts_fmc.html#Configure_SAML_Single_Sig=
nOn_">Configure SAML Single Sign-On</a></section>
                              </section>
                           </nav>
                           <!-- minitoc end -->
                        </article>
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic reference nested2" aria-labell=
edby=3D"ariaid-title11" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"reference_c31_rfh_hy">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title1=
1"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span>=
</span> High Availability Behavior During a Backup
                        </h3>
                        <section class=3D"body refbody">
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_c31_r=
fh_hy__section_k31_rfh_hy">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">When you perform a Backup on a=
 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></=
span> high availability pair, the Backup operation pauses synchronization b=
etween the peers. During this operation, you may continue
                                 using the active <span class=3D"ph"><span =
class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>, but not the standby=
 peer.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">After Backup is completed, syn=
chronization resumes, which briefly disables processes on the active peer. =
During this pause,
                                 the High Availability page briefly display=
s a holding page until all processes resume.
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic reference nested2" aria-labell=
edby=3D"ariaid-title12" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_21618">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title1=
2">Firepower Management Center High Availability Split-Brain</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body refbody">
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_21618__secti=
on_62A7598D0D3B4FA297EC05BD83DE1962">=20
                              	=09
                              <p class=3D"p">If the active <span class=3D"p=
h"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> in a high-a=
vailability pair goes down (due to power issues, network/connectivity issue=
s), you can promote the standby <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firep=
ower Management Center</span></span> to an active state. When the original =
active peer comes up, both peers can assume they are active. This state is =
defined
                                 as 'split-brain'. When this situation occu=
rs, the system prompts you to choose an active appliance, which demotes the=
 other
                                 appliance to standby.=20
                              </p>=20
                              	=09
                              <p class=3D"p">If the active=20
                                 		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">=
Firepower Management Center</span></span>
                                 		  goes down (or disconnects due to a net=
work failure), you may either break high
                                 		  availability or switch roles. The stan=
dby=20
                                 		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">=
Firepower Management Center</span></span>
                                 		  enters a degraded state.
                                 	=09
                              </p>
                              		=09
                              <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D=
"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                 <tbody><tr>
                                    <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" rol=
e=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en=
/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                       <section class=3D"note__content">
                                          <hr>
                                          			=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">Whichever applianc=
e you use as the secondary loses all of its device registrations and policy=
 configurations when you resolve
                                             split-brain. For example, you =
would lose modifications to any policies that existed on the secondary but =
not on the primary.
                                             If the <span class=3D"ph"><spa=
n class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> is in a high avail=
ability split-brain scenario where both appliances are active, and you regi=
ster managed devices and deploy
                                             policies before you resolve sp=
lit-brain, you must export any policies and unregister any managed devices =
from the intended
                                             standby <span class=3D"ph"><sp=
an class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> before re-establi=
shing high availability. You may then register the managed devices and impo=
rt the policies to the intended
                                             active <span class=3D"ph"><spa=
n class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>.=20
                                          </p>
                                          		=09
                                          <hr>
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody></table></div>=20
                              	=20
                           </section>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic task nested2 no_summary_steps"=
 aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title13" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"task_65775BC7775D4=
C33ACD6BBE15B28859E">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title1=
3">Upgrading Firepower Management Centers in a High Availability Pair</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"task_65=
775BC7775D4C33ACD6BBE15B28859E__context_4EB5D7BA11BB4167BC1791FD9B60CD20">=
=20
                              	=09
                              <p class=3D"p">Cisco electronically distribut=
es several different types of updates periodically. These include major and=
 minor upgrades to
                                 the system software. You may need to insta=
ll these updates on <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Managem=
ent Center</span></span>s in a high availability setup.=20
                              </p>
                              		=09
                              <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D=
"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                 <tbody><tr>
                                    <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" rol=
e=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en=
/us/td/i/templates/warn.gif"><br><p><b>Warning</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                       <section class=3D"note__content">
                                          <hr>Make sure that there is at le=
ast one operational <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Managem=
ent Center</span></span> during an upgrade.
                                          <hr>
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody></table></div>=20
                              	=20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"section prereq p" id=3D"task_6=
5775BC7775D4C33ACD6BBE15B28859E__prereq_DD9DF228DE67428D8BA6DDCACC2B3D12">
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">Before you begin</h4>
                              </section>
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p">Read the release notes or advi=
sory text that accompanies the upgrade. The release notes provide important=
 information, including
                                 supported platforms, compatibility, prereq=
uisites, warnings, and specific installation and uninstallation instruction=
s.
                              </p>=20
                              	=20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h4>
                           </section>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"st=
epTable" border=3D"0">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"task_65775BC77=
75D4C33ACD6BBE15B28859E__step_2FCDBD2873FB4FF190930FB9B7513B06">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Access the web i=
nterface of the active <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Mana=
gement Center</span></span> and pause data synchronization; see <a class=3D=
"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/=
configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower_management_center_high_=
availability.html#ID-2242-000004f4">Pausing Communication Between Paired Fi=
repower Management Centers</a>.=20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"task_65775BC77=
75D4C33ACD6BBE15B28859E__step_300B8994396642FFB51D3DCA4FCF566F">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Upgrade the stan=
dby <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span=
></span>; see the upgrade guide.=20
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup stepresu=
lt">When the upgrade completes, the standby unit becomes active. When both
                                          					peers are active, the high a=
vailability pair is in a degraded state
                                          					(split-brain).=20
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Upgrade the othe=
r <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span><=
/span>.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Decide which <sp=
an class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span=
> you want to use as the standby. Any additional devices or policies added =
to the standby after pausing synchronization are
                                          not synced to the active <span cl=
ass=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>. Un=
register only those additional devices and export any configurations you wa=
nt to preserve.
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                          				=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">When you choose a =
new active <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Cente=
r</span></span>, the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Manage=
ment Center</span></span> you designate as secondary will lose device regis=
trations and deployed policy configurations, which are not synced.
                                          </p>
                                          			=09
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"task_65775BC77=
75D4C33ACD6BBE15B28859E__step_9BF0417197394394A295A355E34C23AC">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;5</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Resolve split-br=
ain by choosing the new active <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepo=
wer Management Center</span></span> which has all the latest required confi=
gurations for policies and devices.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic reference nested2" aria-labell=
edby=3D"ariaid-title14" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_32278">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title1=
4">Troubleshooting <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Manageme=
nt Center</span></span> High Availability
                        </h3>
                        <section class=3D"body refbody">
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_32278__secti=
on_591DB9CD548E49169DD1E060E22DD491">
                              		=09
                              <p class=3D"p">This section lists troubleshoo=
ting information for some common <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fire=
power Management Center</span></span> high availability operation errors.
                              </p>
                              		=09
                              <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table width=3D=
"100%" border=3D"1" class=3D"table frame-all" id=3D"id_32278__table_lvd_g5q=
_n1b">
                                 <caption></caption>
                                 <colgroup>
                                    <col style=3D"width:20%">
                                    <col style=3D"width:40%">
                                    <col style=3D"width:40%">
                                 </colgroup>
                                 <thead class=3D"thead">
                                    <tr>
                                       <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"en=
try colsep-1 rowsep-1" id=3D"id_32278__table_lvd_g5q_n1b__entry__1">
                                          							=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">Error</p>
                                          						=09
                                       </th>
                                       <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"en=
try colsep-1 rowsep-1" id=3D"id_32278__table_lvd_g5q_n1b__entry__2">
                                          							=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">Description</p>
                                          						=09
                                       </th>
                                       <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"en=
try colsep-1 rowsep-1" id=3D"id_32278__table_lvd_g5q_n1b__entry__3">
                                          							=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">Solution</p>
                                          						=09
                                       </th>
                                    </tr>
                                 </thead>
                                 <tbody class=3D"tbody">
                                    <tr>
                                       <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1=
" headers=3D"id_32278__table_lvd_g5q_n1b__entry__1 ">
                                          							=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">You must reset you=
r password on the active Firepower Management Center before you can log int=
o the standby</p>
                                          						=09
                                       </td>
                                       <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1=
" headers=3D"id_32278__table_lvd_g5q_n1b__entry__2 ">
                                          							=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">You attempted to l=
og into the standby FMC when a force password reset is enabled for your acc=
ount. </p>
                                          						=09
                                       </td>
                                       <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1=
" headers=3D"id_32278__table_lvd_g5q_n1b__entry__3 ">
                                          							=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">As the database is=
 read-only for a standby FMC, reset the password on the login page of the a=
ctive FMC.</p>
                                          						=09
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                       <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1=
" headers=3D"id_32278__table_lvd_g5q_n1b__entry__1 ">
                                          							=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">500 Internal</p>
                                          						=09
                                       </td>
                                       <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1=
" headers=3D"id_32278__table_lvd_g5q_n1b__entry__2 ">
                                          							=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">May appear when at=
tempting to access the web interface while performing critical <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> high a=
vailability operations, including switching peer roles or pausing and resum=
ing synchronization.
                                          </p>
                                          						=09
                                       </td>
                                       <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1=
" headers=3D"id_32278__table_lvd_g5q_n1b__entry__3 ">
                                          							=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">Wait until the ope=
ration completes before using the web interface. </p>
                                          						=09
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                       <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1=
" headers=3D"id_32278__table_lvd_g5q_n1b__entry__1 ">
                                          							=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">System processes a=
re starting, please wait</p>
                                          							=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">Also, the web inte=
rface does not respond.</p>
                                          						=09
                                       </td>
                                       <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1=
" headers=3D"id_32278__table_lvd_g5q_n1b__entry__2 ">
                                          							=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">May appear when th=
e <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span><=
/span> reboots (manually or while recovering from a power down) during a hi=
gh availability or data synchronization operation.
                                          </p>
                                          						=09
                                       </td>
                                       <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1=
" headers=3D"id_32278__table_lvd_g5q_n1b__entry__3 ">
                                          							=09
                                          <ol class=3D"ol" id=3D"id_32278__=
ol_ylc_r5q_n1b">
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                                									=09
                                                <p class=3D"p">Access the <=
span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></sp=
an> shell and use the <code class=3D"ph codeph">manage_hadc.pl</code> comma=
nd to access the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management=
 Center</span></span>  high availability configuration utility.
                                                </p>
                                                									=09
                                                <table class=3D"olh_note" b=
order=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                                   <tbody><tr>
                                                      <td width=3D"1%" clas=
s=3D"olh_note" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                         <p><b>Note</b></p>=
&nbsp;
                                                      </td>
                                                      <td border=3D"0" clas=
s=3D"olh_note">
                                                         <section class=3D"=
note__content">
                                                            										=09
                                                            <p class=3D"p">=
Run the utility as a root user, using  <code class=3D"ph codeph">sudo</code=
>.
                                                            </p>
                                                            									=09
                                                         </section>
                                                      </td>
                                                   </tr>
                                                </tbody></table>
                                                								=09
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                                									=09
                                                <p class=3D"p">Pause mirror=
ing operations by using option 5.</p>
                                                									=09
                                                <p class=3D"p">Reload the <=
span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></sp=
an> web interface.
                                                </p>
                                                								=09
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                                									=09
                                                <p class=3D"p">Use the web =
interface to resume synchronization. Choose <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Sy=
stem &gt; Integration</span>, then click the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">H=
igh Availability</span> tab and choose <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Resume =
Synchronization</span>.=20
                                                </p>
                                                								=09
                                             </li>
                                          </ol>
                                          						=09
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                 </tbody>
                              </table></div>=20
                              	=20
                           </section>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                  </article>

                        </h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                              		=09
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 			=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">Supported hardware models:<=
/p>
                                 			=09
                                 			=09
                                 <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"ph">MC1000, =
</span><span class=3D"ph">MC1600, </span><span class=3D"ph"> MC2500,</span>

><span class=3D"ph"> MC4500</span><span class=3D"ph">, MC4600 </span></p>
                                 		=09

                                 			=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">The two <span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s in a high ava=
ilability configuration must be the same model.=20
