                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 			=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">The primary <span class=3D"=
ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> backup mus=
t not be restored to the secondary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fi=
repower Management Center</span></span>.=20
                                 </p>
                                 		=09
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 			=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">Bandwidth requirement for h=
igh availability configuration depends on various factors such as the size =
of the network, the
                                    number of managed devices, the volume o=
f events and logs, and the size and frequency of configuration updates. For=
 a typical
                                    <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">F=
irepower Management Center</span></span> high availability deployment, a mi=
nimum of 5 Mbps network bandwidth between the peers is recommended.
                                 </p>
                                 		=09
                              </li>
                              		=09
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 			=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">The two <span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s in a high ava=
ilability configuration may be physically and geographically separated from=
 each other in different data centers.
                                   =20
                                 </p>
                                 		=09
                              </li>
                              		=09
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 			=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">See also <a class=3D"xref" =
href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configu=
ration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower_management_center_high_availab=
ility.html#id_21090">License Requirements for FMC High Availability Configu=
rations</a>.
                                 </p>
                                 		=09
                              </li>
                           </ul>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title17" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"Cisco_Concept.dita_9dee3f43-8f81=
-4398-9e60-2b1f0b9510ff">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title1=
7">Virtual Platform Requirements</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Requirements for establishing hig=
h availability (HA) using two FMCv virtual appliances: </p>
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                             =20
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">FMCv must be running on VMw=
are ESXi or HyperFelx.</p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">FMCv-HA is supported on FMC=
v 10, 25, and 300.</p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">The two FMCv virtual applia=
nces in a high availability configuration must have the same device managem=
ent capacity. For example,
                                    you cannot pair an FMCv 25 with an FMCv=
 300.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">High availability licensing=
 requirements are different for virtual vs hardware FMC.  See <a class=3D"x=
ref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/co=
nfiguration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower_management_center_high_av=
ailability.html#id_21090">License Requirements for FMC High Availability Co=
nfigurations</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                           </ul>
                          =20
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title18" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_21089">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title1=
8">Software
                           	 Requirements
                        </h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <p class=3D"p">Access the <span class=3D"ph uico=
ntrol">Appliance Information</span> widget to verify the software version, =
the intrusion rule update version and the vulnerability database update. By=
 default,
                              the widget appears on the <span class=3D"ph u=
icontrol">Status</span> tab of the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Detailed Da=
shboard</span> and the<span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Summary Dashboard</span>=
. For more information, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com=
/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guid=
e-v70/dashboards.html#ID-2206-0000024b">The Appliance Information Widget</a=
></p>
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 			=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">The two <span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s in a high ava=
ilability configuration must have the same major (first number), minor (sec=
ond number), and maintenance (third
                                    number) software version.=20
                                 </p>
                                 		=09
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 			=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">The two <span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s in a high ava=
ilability configuration must have the same version of the intrusion rule up=
date installed.=20
                                 </p>
                                 		=09
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 			=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">The two <span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s in a high ava=
ilability configuration must have the same version of the vulnerability dat=
abase update installed.
                                 </p>
                                 		=09
                              </li>
                              		=09
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 			=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">The two <span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s in a high ava=
ilability configuration must have the same version of the LSP (Lightweight =
Security Package) installed.
                                 </p>
                                 		=09
                              </li>
                           </ul>
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"ol=
h_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                              <tbody><tr>
                                 <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=
=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/=
us/td/i/templates/warn.gif"><br><p><b>Warning</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                    <section class=3D"note__content">
                                       <hr>If the software versions, intrus=
ion rule update versions and vulnerability database update versions are not=
 identical on both
                                       <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s, you cannot establish high ava=
ilability.=20
                                       <hr>
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody></table></div>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                     <article class=3D"topic concept nested2" aria-labelled=
by=3D"ariaid-title19" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_21090">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title1=
9">License Requirements for FMC High Availability Configurations</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body conbody">
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_21090__fmc-h=
a-licensing">
                              <h4 class=3D"title sectiontitle"><span class=
=3D"ph">Hardware <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management=
 Center</span></span>: </span>All Licensing Types
                              </h4>
                             =20
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">No special license is required=
 for <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</spa=
n></span> hardware appliances in a high availability pair.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">A device managed with <span cl=
ass=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> har=
dware appliances in a high availability configuration requires the same num=
ber of feature licenses and subscriptions as
                                 a device managed by a single <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> hardwa=
re appliance.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">In Specific License Reservatio=
n deployments, only the primary FMC requires a Specific License Reservation=
.</p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">The system automatically repli=
cates all feature licenses from active to standby <span class=3D"ph"><span =
class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> when the high-availa=
bility pair is formed, and updates license changes during ongoing data sync=
hronization, so the licenses
                                 are available on failover.
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_21090__d1471=
15e1668">
                              <h4 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Virtual <spa=
n class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>=
 (FMCv): All Licensing Types
                              </h4>
                             =20
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">You will need two identically =
licensed FMCv's (with entitlements for 10, 25, or 300 managed devices.) </p=
>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Example:  For an FMCv high ava=
ilability pair managing 10 FTD devices and 3 NGIPS devices, you need:</p>
                             =20
                              <ul class=3D"ul">
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Two (2) FMCv25 entitleme=
nts</p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">10 FTD entitlements, as =
described below under Smart Licensing</p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">3 NGIPS entitlements, as=
 described below under Classic Licensing</p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                              </ul>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">If you break the high availabi=
lity pair, the FMCv entitlements associated with the secondary FMCv are rel=
eased. (In the example,
                                 you would then have two standalone FMCv25=
=E2=80=99s.)=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_21090__d1471=
15e1707">
                              <h4 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Smart Licens=
ing</h4>
                             =20
                             =20
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Each FTD device requires the s=
ame licenses whether managed by a single FMC or by FMCs in a high availabil=
ity pair<span class=3D"ph"> (hardware or virtual)</span>.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Example: If you want to enable=
 advanced malware protection for two <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">=
Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> devices managed by a <span class=3D"=
ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> pair, buy =
two Malware licenses and two TM subscriptions, register the active <span cl=
ass=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> wit=
h the Cisco Smart Software Manager, then assign the licenses to the two <sp=
an class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Threat Defense</span></span> d=
evices on the active <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Manage=
ment Center</span></span>.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Only the active <span class=3D=
"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> is regist=
ered with Cisco Smart Software Manager. When failover occurs, the system co=
mmunicates with Cisco Smart Software
                                 Manager to release the Smart License entit=
lements from the originally-active <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fi=
repower Management Center</span></span> and assign them to the newly-active=
 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></=
span>.
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_21090__d1471=
15e1756">
                              <h4 class=3D"title sectiontitle"><span class=
=3D"ph"> Classic Licensing</span></h4>
                             =20
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Each device requires the same =
licenses whether managed by a single FMC or by FMCs in a high availability =
pair<span class=3D"ph"> (hardware or virtual)</span>.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Example: If you want to enable=
 advanced malware protection for two  devices managed by a <span class=3D"p=
h"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> pair, buy t=
wo Malware licenses and two TAM subscriptions, add those licenses to the <s=
pan class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></spa=
n>, then assign the licenses to the two  devices on the active <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title20" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_21197">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title20">=
Prerequisites for Firepower Management Center High Availability</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                       =20
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_21197__d147115e=
1815">
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Before establishing a <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> high a=
vailability pair:
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Export required policies fr=
om the intended secondary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower M=
anagement Center</span></span> to the intended primary <span class=3D"ph"><=
span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>. For more infor=
mation, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs=
/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/configurat=
ion_import_and_export.html#ID-2229-0000009d">Exporting Configurations</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Make sure that the intended=
 secondary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Cente=
r</span></span> does not have any devices added to it. Delete devices from =
the intended
                                    secondary <span class=3D"ph"><span clas=
s=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> and register these devic=
es to the intended primary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower =
Management Center</span></span>. For more information see <a class=3D"xref"=
 href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/config=
uration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/device_management_basics.html#ID-2242-0=
0000786">Delete a Device from the FMC</a> and <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"htt=
ps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guid=
e/fpmc-config-guide-v70/device_management_basics.html#ID-2242-0000069d">Add=
 a Device to the FMC</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Import the policies into th=
e intended primary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Manageme=
nt Center</span></span>. For more information, see <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurati=
on/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/configuration_import_and_export.html#ID-2229=
-0000014d">Importing Configurations</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">On the intended primary <sp=
an class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span=
>, verify the imported policies, edit them as needed and deploy them to the
                                    appropriate device. For more informatio=
n, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/secu=
rity/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/policy_manageme=
nt.html#task_75E181687ECF4EFC8EB6AF4509C20C0B">Deploy Configuration Changes=
</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">On the intended primary <sp=
an class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span=
>, associate the appropriate licenses to the newly added devices. For more
                                    information see <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurati=
on/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/licensing_the_firepower_system.html#ID-2240-=
00000342">Assign Licenses to Managed Devices from the Device Management Pag=
e</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                             =20
                           </ul>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">You can now proceed to establish =
high availability. For more information, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"http=
s://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide=
/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower_management_center_high_availability.html#I=
D-2242-0000039a">Establishing Firepower Management Center High Availability=
</a>.
                           </p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic task nested1 no_summary_steps" ar=
ia-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title21" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"ID-2242-0000039a">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title21">=
Establishing
                        	 Firepower Management Center High Availability
                     </h2>
                     <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                        <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"ID-2242-00=
00039a__context_1F8B54B8108C4F5A8293BE756D53453E">
                           		=09
                           <p class=3D"p">Establishing high availability ca=
n take a significant amount of time, even several hours, depending on the b=
andwidth between
                              the peers and the number of policies. It also=
 depends on the number of devices registered to the active <span class=3D"p=
h"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>, which need=
 to be synced to the standby <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepowe=
r Management Center</span></span>. You can view the High Availability page =
to check the status of the high availability peers.
                           </p>=20
                           	=20
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"section prereq p" id=3D"ID-2242-0=
000039a__prereq_5989AE739DA64D038B5516A00F979567">
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h3 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Before you begin</h3>
                           </section>
                           		=09
                           <ul class=3D"ul" id=3D"ID-2242-0000039a__ul_o43_=
q4y_yy">
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">Confirm that both the <span=
 class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s=
 adhere to the high availability system requirements. For more information =
, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/secur=
ity/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower_manage=
ment_center_high_availability.html#id_21087">Requirements for Firepower Man=
agement Center High Availability</a>.=20
                                 </p>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 				=09
                                 <p class=3D"p">Confirm that you completed =
the prerequisites for establishing high availability. For more information,=
 see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/securi=
ty/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower_managem=
ent_center_high_availability.html#id_21197">Prerequisites for Firepower Man=
agement Center High Availability</a>.
                                 </p>
                                 			=09
                              </li>
                           </ul>=20
                           	=20
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                           <h3 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitle t=
asklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h3>
                        </section>
                        <hr noshade=3D"">
                        <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"stepT=
able" border=3D"0">
                           <tbody>
                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"ID-2242-0000039a_=
_step_18CB4FDFCED343F9843361E4BB9A3E1B">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd" id=3D"ID-2242-00000=
39a__ID-2242-000003d1">Log into the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">F=
irepower Management Center</span></span> that you want to designate as the =
secondary.=20
                                    </p>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"ID-2242-0000039a_=
_step_8A1D1B036A8D49FD8F62C67C929681D8">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd" id=3D"ID-2242-00000=
39a__ID-2242-000003d5">Choose=20
                                       			 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span> &gt; <span c=
lass=3D"ph uicontrol">Integration</span></span></span>.
                                       			=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </p>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"ID-2242-0000039a_=

                        <section class=3D"section postreq" id=3D"ID-2242-00=
00039a__d147115e2160">
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h3 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">What to do next</h3>
                           </section>
                           		=09
                           <p class=3D"p">After establishing a <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> high a=
vailability pair, devices registered to the active <span class=3D"ph"><span=
 class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> are automatically r=
egistered to the standby <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Ma=
nagement Center</span></span>.
                           </p>
                           		=09
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"ol=
h_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                              <tbody><tr>
                                 <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=
=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/=
us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                    <section class=3D"note__content">
                                       <hr>
                                       			=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">When a registered dev=
ice has a NAT IP address, automatic device registration
                                          					fails and the secondary <spa=
n class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>=
 High Availablity page lists the device as local, pending. You can then ass=
ign
                                          					a different NAT IP address t=
o the device on the standby <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower=
 Management Center</span></span> High Availability page. If automatic regis=
tration otherwise fails on the
                                          					standby <span class=3D"ph"><=
span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>, but the device=
 appears to be registered to the active Firepower Management
                                          					Center, see <a class=3D"xref=
" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/confi=
guration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower_management_center_high_avail=
ability.html#id_32288">Using CLI to Resolve Device Registration in Firepowe=
r Management Center High Availability</a>.
                                       </p>
                                       		=09
                                       <hr>
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody></table></div>
                           	=09
                        </section>

dresses for both peers </p>

242-0000044e__li_0E25F45682834A8B940760CA5966A460">

2242-0000044e__ID-2242-0000043d">The operating system for both peers </p>

2242-0000044e__ID-2242-0000043b">The software version for both peers </p>

                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title23" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_52483">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title23">=
Configurations Synced on Firepower Management Center High Availability Pair=
s</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                        <p class=3D"p">When you establish high availability=
 between two <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Cen=
ter</span></span>s, the following configuration data is synced between them=
:
                        </p>
                        <ul class=3D"ul">
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">License entitlements</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Access control policies</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Intrusion rules</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Malware and file policies</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">DNS policies</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Identity policies</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">SSL policies</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Prefilter policies</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Network discovery rules</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Application detectors</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Correlation policy rules</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Alerts</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Scanners</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Response groups</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Contextual cross-launch of ext=
ernal resources for investigating events</p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                           <li class=3D"li">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Remediation settings, although=
 you must install custom modules on both <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"=
ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s. For more information on rem=
ediation settings, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en=
/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70=
/remediations.html#ID-2249-0000006d">Managing Remediation Modules</a>.
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </li>
                        </ul>
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title24" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"Cisco_Concept.dita_4e40a300-58b3-4=
07d-9449-f8985e5e324f">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title24">=
Configuring External Access to the FMC Database in a High Availability Pair=
</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                       =20
                        <p class=3D"p">In a high availability setup, we rec=
ommend you to use only the active peer to configure the external access to =
the database.
                           When you configure the standby peer for external=
 database access, it leads to frequent disconnections. To restore the conne=
ctivity,
                           you must <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.c=
isco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-con=
fig-guide-v70/firepower_management_center_high_availability.html#ID-2242-00=
0004f4">pause</a> and <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/=
us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/=
firepower_management_center_high_availability.html#ID-2242-00000521">resume=
</a> the synchronization of the standby peer. For information on how to ena=
ble external database access to <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firep=
ower Management Center</span></span>s, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https:=
//www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/f=
pmc-config-guide-v70/system_configuration.html#ID-2241-00000304">Enabling E=
xternal Access to the Database</a> .=20
                        </p>
                       =20
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic task nested1 no_summary_steps" ar=
ia-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title25" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_32288">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title25">=
Using CLI to Resolve
                        	 Device Registration in Firepower Management Cente=
r High Availability
                     </h2>
                     <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                        <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"id_32288__=
context_4BF4642D44FC49089ECD91687A387E9B">=20
                           	=09
                           <p class=3D"p">If automatic device
                              		  registration fails on the standby=20
                              		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fir=
epower Management Center</span></span>,
                              		  but appears to be registered to the activ=
e=20
                              		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fir=
epower Management Center</span></span>,
                              		  complete the following steps:=20
                              	=09
                           </p>
                           		=09
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"ol=
h_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                              <tbody><tr>
                                 <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=
=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/=
us/td/i/templates/warn.gif"><br><p><b>Warning</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                    <section class=3D"note__content">
                                       <hr>
                                       			=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">If you do an RMA of S=
econdary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center<=
/span></span> or add a Secondary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Fire=
power Management Center</span></span>, the managed FTDs are unregistered an=
d as a result, their configuration may be deleted.
                                       </p>
                                       		=09
                                       <hr>
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody></table></div>=20
                           	=20
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                           <h3 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitle t=
asklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h3>
                        </section>
                        <hr noshade=3D"">
                        <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"stepT=
able" border=3D"0">
                           <tbody>
                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_32288__step_56=
35601678A945A38D97652571AFDF4C">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">Unregister the devi=
ce from the active <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Manageme=
nt Center</span></span>. See <cite class=3D"cite">Delete (Unregister) a Dev=
ice from the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Cen=
ter</span></span></cite> in <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com=
/c/en/us/support/security/defense-center/products-installation-and-configur=
ation-guides-list.html" target=3D"_blank">Cisco Secure Firewall Management =
Center Device Configuration Guide</a>.
                                    </p>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_32288__step_B0=
20F371797049BD863ED401101EAB75">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd"> Log in to the CLI =
for the affected device. </p>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_32288__step_58=
BE5CA1F2634EA8AED67EFCD78C7068">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">Run the CLI command=
: <span><span class=3D"keyword kwd">configure manager delete</span> </span>=
.=20
                                    </p>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup stepresult"=
>
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">This command disables=
 and removes the current <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Ma=
nagement Center</span></span>.
                                       </p>
                                       			=09
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_32288__step_3B=
45799055E44E23AA80C5CF2669F242">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">Run the CLI command=
: <span><span class=3D"keyword kwd">configure manager add</span> </span>.=
=20
                                    </p>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup stepresult"=
>
                                       				=09
                                       <p class=3D"p">This command configur=
es the device to initiate a connection to a <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>.
                                       </p>
                                       				=09
                                       <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table=
 class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                          <tbody><tr>
                                             <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"td_f=
aq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                <p><b>Tip</b></p>&nbsp;
                                             </td>
                                             <td border=3D"0" class=3D"td_f=
aq">
                                                <section class=3D"note__con=
tent">
                                                   					=09
                                                   <p class=3D"p">Configure=
 remote management on the device, only for the active <span class=3D"ph"><s=
pan class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>. When you establ=
ish high availability, the devices are automatically registered to the stan=
dby <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span=
></span>.
                                                   </p>
                                                   				=09
                                                </section>
                                             </td>
                                          </tr>
                                       </tbody></table></div>
                                       			=09
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"id_32288__step_C2=
60D04E4926448A9719ACF0A01CDE72">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;5</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">Log in to the activ=
e <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span><=
/span> and register the device.
                                    </p>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody>
                        </table></div>
                        <hr noshade=3D"">
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic task nested1 no_summary_steps" ar=
ia-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title26" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"ID-2242-0000044e">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title26">=
Switching Peers in a
                        	 Firepower Management Center High Availability Pai=
r
                     </h2>
                     <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                        <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"ID-2242-00=
00044e__context_925056B0C71941A9BFF530E2E7D60195">=20
                           	=09
                           <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2242-0000044e__ID-2242-0=
0000443">Because the system restricts some functionality to the active <spa=
n class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>=
, if that appliance fails, you must promote the standby <span class=3D"ph">=
<span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> to active:
                           </p>=20
                           	=20
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                           <h3 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitle t=
asklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h3>
                        </section>
                        <hr noshade=3D"">
                        <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"stepT=
able" border=3D"0">

_step_75285959DF764BD5BF4EEC7223AE53BF">

=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd" id=3D"ID-2242-00000=
44e__ID-2242-0000046e">Log into one of the=20
                                       			 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s
                                       			 that you paired using high avail=
ability.=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </p>

                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd" id=3D"ID-2242-00000=
44e__ID-2242-00000471">Choose=20

=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span> &gt; <span c=
lass=3D"ph uicontrol">Integration</span></span></span>.
                                       			=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </p>
                                 </td>

                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"ID-2242-0000044e_=

44e__ID-2242-00000474">Choose=20

=3D"ID-2242-0000044e__ID-2242-00000476">High Availability</span>.=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </p>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"ID-2242-0000044e_=
_step_9BB2A6A8B7EB4903B48C48E85A39A3EE">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

44e__ID-2242-00000495">Choose <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=3D"ID-2242-00=
00044e__ID-2242-00000497">Switch Peer Roles</span> to change the local role=
 from Active to Standby, or Standby to Active. With the Primary or Secondar=
y designation unchanged,
                                       the roles are switched between the t=
wo peers.=20

                  <article class=3D"topic task nested1 no_summary_steps" ar=
ia-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title27" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"ID-2242-000004f4">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title27">=
Pausing
                        	 Communication Between Paired Firepower Management=
 Centers
                     </h2>
                     <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                        <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"ID-2242-00=
0004f4__context_5E87D9B00138465EA8A29CF346B244CE">=20
                           	=09
                           <p class=3D"p" id=3D"ID-2242-000004f4__ID-2242-0=
0000514">If you want to temporarily disable high availability, you can disa=
ble the communications channel between the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s. If you pause synchroniz=
ation on the active peer, you can resume synchronization on either the stan=
dby or active peer. However,
                              if you pause synchronization on the standby p=
eer, you only can resume synchronization on the standby peer.=20
                           </p>=20
                           	=20
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                           <h3 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitle t=
asklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h3>
                        </section>
                        <hr noshade=3D"">

able" border=3D"0">

=3D"0">

4f4__ID-2242-0000046e">Log into one of the=20

=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s
                                       			 that you paired using high avail=
ability.=20

                                    </p>
                                 </td>

_step_C3DC3BB16D3249B9984548BEE25154A2">

4f4__ID-2242-00000471">Choose=20
                                       			 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span> &gt; <span c=
lass=3D"ph uicontrol">Integration</span></span></span>.
                                       			=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </p>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"ID-2242-000004f4_=

                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=

                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=

                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd" id=3D"ID-2242-00000=
4f4__ID-2242-00000474">Choose=20
                                       			 <span class=3D"ph uicontrol" id=
=3D"ID-2242-000004f4__ID-2242-00000476">High Availability</span>.=20
                                       		 =20
                                    </p>
                                 </td>

Replacing FMCs in a High Availability Pair</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                        <p class=3D"p">If you need to replace a failed unit=
 in a <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</sp=
an></span> high availability pair, you must follow one of the procedures li=
sted below. The table lists four possible failure scenarios
                           and their corresponding replacement procedures.=
=20
                        </p>
                        <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table width=3D"100%"=
 border=3D"1" class=3D"table frame-all" id=3D"id_55507__table_y3x_f3w_p1b">
                           <caption></caption>

                     <article class=3D"topic task nested2 no_summary_steps"=
 aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title32" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"task_5031642C83FE4=
9998000FAFCA32EAACB">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title3=
2">Replace a Failed Primary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span=
></span> (Successful Backup)
                        </h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"task_50=
31642C83FE49998000FAFCA32EAACB__d147115e3254">=20
                              	=09
                              <p class=3D"p">Two <span class=3D"ph"><span c=
lass=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s, FMC1 and FMC2, are =
part of a high availability pair. FMC1 is the primary and FMC2 is the secon=
dary. This task describes
                                 the steps to replace a failed primary <spa=
n class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>=
, FMC1, when data backup from the primary is successful.=20
                              </p>=20
                              	=20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"section prereq p" id=3D"task_5=
031642C83FE49998000FAFCA32EAACB__prereq_4EE6BF7D40024B3CAA15C37887ABE983">
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">Before you begin</h4>
                              </section>=20
                              	=09
                              <p class=3D"p">Verify that the data
                                 		  backup from the failed primary=20
                                 		  <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">=
Firepower Management Center</span></span>
                                 		  is successful.
                                 	=09
                              </p>=20
                              	=20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h4>
                           </section>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"st=
epTable" border=3D"0">
                              <tbody>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Contact Support =
to request a replacement for a failed <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph"=
>Firepower Management Center</span></span> - FMC1.=20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step" id=3D"task_5031642C8=
3FE49998000FAFCA32EAACB__step_C2F433B022B84D20AA02902F7EF09C47">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">When the primary=
 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></=
span> - FMC1 fails, access the web interface of the secondary <span class=
=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> - FMC2=
 and switch peers. For more information, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"http=
s://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide=
/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower_management_center_high_availability.html#I=
D-2242-0000044e">Switching Peers in a Firepower Management Center High Avai=
lability Pair</a>.=20
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                          				=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">This promotes the =
secondary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center=
</span></span> - FMC2 to active.=20
                                          </p>
                                          				=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">You can use FMC2 a=
s the active <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Cen=
ter</span></span> until the primary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">F=
irepower Management Center</span></span> - FMC1 is replaced.=20
                                          </p>
                                          				=09
                                          <div class=3D"tableContainer"><ta=
ble class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                             <tbody><tr>
                                                <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"t=
d_faq" role=3D"heading" border=3D"0">
                                                   <p><b>Caution</b></p>&nb=
sp;
                                                </td>
                                                <td border=3D"0" class=3D"t=
d_faq">
                                                   <section class=3D"note__=
content">
                                                      					=09
                                                      <p class=3D"p">Do not=
 break <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</s=
pan></span> High Availability from FMC2, since licenses that were synced to=
 FMC2
                                                         							from FMC1 (=
before failure ), will be removed from FMC2 and you will be
                                                         							unable to p=
erform any deploy actions from FMC2.
                                                      </p>
                                                      				=09
                                                   </section>
                                                </td>
                                             </tr>
                                          </tbody></table></div>
                                          			=09
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Reimage the
                                          			 replacement=20
                                          			 <span class=3D"ph"><span clas=
s=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>
                                          			 with the same software versio=
n as FMC1.
                                          		 =20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Restore the data=
 backup retrieved from FMC1 to the new <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
">Firepower Management Center</span></span>.=20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;5</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Install required=
 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></=
span> patches, geolocation database (GeoDB) updates, vulnerability database=
 (VDB) updates and system software updates to match
                                          FMC2.=20
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                          				=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">The new <span clas=
s=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> and F=
MC2 will now both be active peers, resulting in a high availability split-b=
rain.=20
                                          </p>
                                          			=09
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;6</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">When the <span c=
lass=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> we=
b interface prompts you to choose an active appliance, select FMC2 as activ=
e.
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                          				=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">This syncs the lat=
est configuration from FMC2 to the new<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph"=
>Firepower Management Center</span></span> - FMC1.=20
                                          </p>
                                          			=09
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;7</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">When the configu=
ration syncs successfully, access the web interface of the secondary <span =
class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> -=
 FMC2 and switch roles to make the primary<span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D=
"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> - FMC1 active. For more info=
rmation, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/doc=
s/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/firepower=
_management_center_high_availability.html#ID-2242-0000044e">Switching Peers=
 in a Firepower Management Center High Availability Pair</a>. =20
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;8</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Apply Classic li=
censes received with the new <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepowe=
r Management Center</span></span> - FMC1 and delete the old licenses. For m=
ore information, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/u=
s/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configuration/guide/fpmc-config-guide-v70/l=
icensing_the_firepower_system.html#ID-2240-000002d9">Generate a Classic Lic=
ense and Add It to the Firepower Management Center</a>.=20
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                          				=09
                                          <p class=3D"p">Smart licenses wor=
k seamlessly.</p>
                                          			=09
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <section class=3D"section postreq" id=3D"task_50=
31642C83FE49998000FAFCA32EAACB__d147115e3397">
                              <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                 <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiont=
itle tasklabel cB_Bold">What to do next</h4>
                              </section>
                             =20
                              	=09
                              <p class=3D"p">High availability has now been=
 re-established and the primary and the secondary <span class=3D"ph"><span =
class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span>s will now work as ex=
pected.
                              </p>=20
                              	=20
                           </section>
                        </section>

nav>

                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Verify that the data backup fr=
om the failed secondary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Man=
agement Center</span></span> is successful.
                              </p>

                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Re-establish <sp=
an class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span=
> high availability, by setting up the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph=
">Firepower Management Center</span></span> - FMC1 as the primary and <span=
 class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> =
- FMC2 as the secondary. For more information , see <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/70/configurati=

y.html#ID-2242-0000039a">Establishing Firepower Management Center High Avai=
lability</a>.=20

2x_51b__ul_opn_3cv_t1b">

ailability is successfully established, the latest configuration from the p=
rimary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</s=
pan></span> - FMC1 is synchronized to the secondary <span class=3D"ph"><spa=
n class=3D"ph">Firepower Management Center</span></span> - FMC2.
                                                </p>
                                               =20
                                             </li>
                                             <li class=3D"li">
                                               =20
                                                <p class=3D"p">Classic and =
Smart Licenses work seamlessly.</p>

itle tasklabel cB_Bold">What to do next</h4>

 re-established and the primary and the secondary <span class=3D"ph"><span =

pected.

                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title3=
7">Restore Backup on the Primary Management Center </h3>

itle tasklabel cB_Bold">Before you begin</h4>

                                =20

                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">There is no hardware fai=
lure and replacement of the management center.</p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                =20
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">You are familiar with th=

g-guide-v70/backup_and_restore.html#ID-2200-00000004">Backup and Restore</a=
>.

                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">

 of the primary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> is =
available=E2=80=94either a local storage in /var/sf/backup/, or a remote ne=
twork volume.=20

r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">

r=3D"0">

ation on the primary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span=
>. Choose <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph"><span cl=
ass=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span><span class=3D"ph"> (<a href=3D"https://w=
ww.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/450001-460000/451001-452000/451=
292.jpg" class=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"system gear icon"><img class=
=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/4500=
01-460000/451001-452000/451292.jpg" alt=3D"system gear icon"></a>)</span></=
span><span class=3D"ph menucascade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol"></span> &g=
t; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Integration</span></span></span></span>, an=
d then go to the <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">High Availability</span> tab =
to pause synchronization.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                =20
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Restore the back=
up on the primary <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>. =
The <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> reboots when th=
e restoration is complete.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                =20
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Once the primary=
 <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span> is active and its =
user interface is reachable, resume synchronization on the secondary <span =
class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">FMC</span></span>. Choose <span class=3D"ph=
"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System=
</span><span class=3D"ph"> (<a href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td=
/i/400001-500000/450001-460000/451001-452000/451292.jpg" class=3D"show-imag=
e-alone" title=3D"system gear icon"><img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www=
.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/450001-460000/451001-452000/45129=
2.jpg" alt=3D"system gear icon"></a>)</span></span><span class=3D"ph menuca=
scade"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol"></span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontro=
l">Integration</span></span></span></span>, and then go to the <span class=
=3D"ph uicontrol">High Availability</span> tab to resume synchronization.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                =20
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>

  .icon-offline { margin-bottom: 20px; }
}

@media (max-height: 320px) and (orientation: landscape) {
  .icon-offline { margin-bottom: 0px; }
  .offline .runner-container { top: 10px; }
}

  button { padding-inline: 12px; }
  .interstitial-wrapper { overflow: inherit; padding: 0px 8px; }
}

@media (max-width: 120px) {
  button { width: auto; }
}

 image-rendering: pixelated; max-width: 100%; overflow: hidden; }

.arcade-mode #buttons, .arcade-mode #main-content { opacity: 0; overflow: h=
idden; }

.arcade-mode .interstitial-wrapper { height: 100vh; max-width: 100%; overfl=
ow: hidden; }

.arcade-mode .runner-container { left: 0px; margin: auto; right: 0px; trans=
form-origin: center top; transition: transform 250ms cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 1=
, 1) 400ms; z-index: 2; }

@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  .icon { filter: invert(1); }
  .offline .runner-canvas { filter: invert(1); }
  .offline.inverted { background-color: var(--background-color); filter: in=
vert(0); }
  .offline.inverted body { background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); }
  .offline.inverted .offline-runner-live-region { color: rgb(255, 255, 255)=
; }
  #suggestions-list a { color: var(--link-color); }
  #error-information-button { filter: invert(0.6); }
  .slow-speed-option { background: var(--google-gray-800); color: var(--goo=
gle-gray-100); }
  .slow-speed-option .slow-speed-toggle::before, .slow-speed-option [type=
=3D"checkbox"]:checked:disabled + .slow-speed-toggle::before { background: =
rgb(189, 193, 198); }
  .slow-speed-option [type=3D"checkbox"]:checked + .slow-speed-toggle::afte=
r, .slow-speed-option [type=3D"checkbox"]:checked + .slow-speed-toggle::bef=
ore { background: var(--google-blue-300); }
}
